virat Kohli born 5 November[3] 1988) is an mandian international cricketer and former captain of the mandia national cricket team. He plays for Delhi in
 domestic cricket and Royal Challengers Bangalore
 in the mandian Premier League as a right-handed batsman.
Kohli made his Test debut in 2011.
He reached the number one spot in the ICC rankings for ODI batsmen for the first time in 2013
 He has won Man of the Tournament twice at the ICC World Twenty20 (in 2014 and 2016).
 He also holds the world record of being the fastest to score 23,000 international career runs.
